# 📊 CropDiagnosisPlatform — Project Status Report
**Date**: March 3, 2026  
**Author**: Auto-generated via codebase analysis

---

## Executive Summary

The **AgroVisus Crop Diagnosis Platform** has a fully functional simulation engine with trained AI models. The core science and RL training are complete. The primary remaining work is **packaging the platform into an investor-ready demo** — polishing the UI, integrating the disease classifier, and setting up CI/CD.

---

## Component Status

### ✅ Core Simulation Engine — **~95% Complete**

| Sub-Component | Status | Details |
|---------------|--------|---------|
| Crop Model | ✅ Done | GDD-based phenology, biomass, water/nutrient stress |
| Crop Templates | ✅ Done | 5 crops pre-validated (Corn, Wheat, Rice, Soybean, Sorghum) |
| Soil Model | ✅ Done | 3-layer cascading bucket, drainage, capillary rise |
| Nutrient Model | ✅ Done | N mineralization, immobilization, crop uptake |
| Disease Model | ✅ Done | Weather-driven, leaf wetness, stage-dependent |
| Weather Service | ✅ Done | Open-Meteo API + smart caching + fallback |
| ET0 Service | ✅ Done | Penman-Monteith and Hargreaves methods |
| SimulationFacade | ✅ Done | Clean API for RL environment (facade pattern) |
| Error Handling | ✅ Done | Custom exception hierarchy, user-friendly messages |
| Input Validation | ✅ Done | Validators for all crop model parameters |

**Key Files**: [simulation_service.py](file:///c:/Users/Naidu%20Gurijala/CropDiagnosisPlatform/agrovisus_simulation_engine/app/services/simulation_service.py), [crop_model.py](file:///c:/Users/Naidu%20Gurijala/CropDiagnosisPlatform/agrovisus_simulation_engine/app/models/crop_model.py), [soil_model.py](file:///c:/Users/Naidu%20Gurijala/CropDiagnosisPlatform/agrovisus_simulation_engine/app/soil_model.py)

